# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:7
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_0c2aa4f4:

    # pc "I kind of miss Brazil."
    pc "Tenho um pouco de saudades do Brasil."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:8
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_2ec566c7:

    # sc "I bet. Was it nice there?"
    sc "Aposto que sim. Era bom lá?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:9
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_ef088408:

    # pc "It was, most of the time."
    pc "Era, na maior parte das vezes."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:10
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_ffefa487:

    # sc "Most of the time?"
    sc "Na maior parte das vezes?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:11
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_f6155a33:

    # pc "Well the places that I stayed at were very nice."
    pc "Bem, os sítios onde fiquei eram muito bons."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:12
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_444ece6f:

    # pc "But Brazil has a sort of split-personality."
    pc "Mas o Brasil tem uma espécie de dupla personalidade."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:13
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_9247b82f:

    # pc "It's absolutely beautiful in most of the places that I stayed."
    pc "É absolutamente lindo na maioria dos sítios onde fiquei."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:14
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_6ce76dfd:

    # pc "But occasionally, I saw the other side, where people were so poor and hungry and had no way to better themselves."
    pc "Mas, ocasionalmente, vi o outro lado, onde as pessoas eram tão pobres e famintas e não tinham como melhorar a sua vida."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:15
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_64352ea1:

    # sc "That must have been eye-opening."
    sc "Isso deve ter sido revelador."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:16
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_ad0a9fab:

    # pc "It was. I know that people are like that in places,"
    pc "Foi. Eu sei que as pessoas são assim em alguns lugares,"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:17
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_b47c5612:

    # pc "But it was so strange to see all of that, then go back to the dorm where I was living and nobody seemed to care."
    pc "Mas foi tão estranho ver tudo isso e depois voltar para o dormitório onde eu morava e ninguém parecia se importar."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:18
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_ba9df9c6:

    # sc "We tend to ignore the nasty things in life that don't affect us personally."
    sc "Temos a tendência de ignorar as coisas desagradáveis da vida que não nos afetam pessoalmente."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:19
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_34e34dc1:

    # sc "It's a sort of coping mechanism. If we were constantly worried about every bad thing happening, we'd probably have a stroke."
    sc "É uma espécie de mecanismo de defesa. Se estivéssemos constantemente preocupados com todas as coisas más que acontecem, provavelmente teríamos um AVC."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:20
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_e46768d7:

    # pc "I guess so, it's just hard to put some of that stuff out of my mind."
    pc "Acho que sim, mas é difícil tirar algumas dessas coisas da minha cabeça."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:21
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_2426cfe6:

    # sc "You shouldn't. You should keep it there. It will make you a better person."
    sc "Não devias. Deves mantê-las lá. Isso vai tornar-te uma pessoa melhor."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:22
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_4a449be8:

    # sc "Know that these things are happening, and know that you are privileged to have the life that you have."
    sc "Sabe que estas coisas estão a acontecer e sabe que tens o privilégio de ter a vida que tens."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:23
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_e88d7ffc:

    # pc "You're right."
    pc "Tens razão."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:25
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_067380d2:

    # sc "You have a good heart. Have you seen The Breakfast Club?"
    sc "Tens um bom coração. Já viste o «The Breakfast Club»?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:28
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_a6773fcb:

    # pc "Sure. Everybody has seen that, right?"
    pc "Claro. Toda a gente já viu isso, certo?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:30
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_8c93b784:

    # pc "I haven't seen it."
    pc "Eu não vi."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:31
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_14e2d7b8:

    # sc "Well there's a line in it that Ally Sheedy says."
    sc "Bem, há uma frase que a Ally Sheedy diz."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:32
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_314554fe:

    # sc "She says, \"When you grow up, your heart dies.\""
    sc "Ela diz: «Quando cresces, o teu coração morre.»"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:33
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_67060d07:

    # sc "And it's true for a lot of people. As they grow up, they become jaded and cynical and stop caring about things."
    sc "E é verdade para muitas pessoas. À medida que crescem, tornam-se cínicas e desiludidas e deixam de se importar com as coisas."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:34
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_9123a037:

    # sc "But you're still young. You have a good heart. Don't let it die, okay?"
    sc "Mas tu ainda és jovem. Tens um bom coração. Não o deixes morrer, está bem?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:35
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_dd9a629d:

    # pc "I won't."
    pc "Não vou deixar."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:37
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_37653c95:

    # sc "Okay, well you better get to class."
    sc "Está bem, é melhor ires para a aula."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:38
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_a8c43555:

    # pc "Okay, I'll see you next time Gertrude."
    pc "Está bem, até à próxima, Gertrude."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:39
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_1b784c07:

    # sc "Bye, [pcname]."
    sc "Adeus, [pcname]."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:40
translate portuguese counselorconversation5_e4b88e88:

    # "With that, I stand up and head to class."
    "Dito isto, levanto-me e dirijo-me para a aula."

